  "response": "Septum piercings are typically done by a professional piercer using the following steps:\n\n1. Consultation and marking\n- The piercer examines the nose anatomy\n- Marks the ideal placement using a surgical pen\n- Identifies the \"sweet spot\" (thin piece of skin between the cartilage)\n\n2. Preparation\n- Cleans the area with an antiseptic solution\n- Uses a medical-grade clamp to hold the skin in place\n\n3. Piercing process\n- Uses a hollow piercing needle (usually 14 or 16 gauge)\n- Quickly passes the needle through the marked \"sweet spot\"\n- Immediately inserts the chosen jewelry (usually a circular barbell or horseshoe ring)\n\n4. Aftercare\n- Provides instructions for cleaning and healing\n- Recommends saline solution for cleaning\n- Advises avoiding touching or moving the piercing during healing\n\nThe entire procedure typically takes only a few minutes and is done under sterile conditions. Healing time is usually 6-8 weeks, though full healing can take several months.\n\nImportant: Always have a professional piercer perform this type of piercing to minimize risks of infection or improper placement.",
